### Declarative User Creation API Validation with Effect Http

Source: https://github.com/pauljphilp/effectpatterns/blob/main/rules/rules.md

This snippet shows a declarative approach to validating incoming JSON request bodies for user creation using Effect's Http module and Schema. It automatically handles validation errors, returning a 400 Bad Request with detailed messages, and ensures type safety for successful requests. This is contrasted with an anti-pattern of manual JSON parsing and validation.

```typescript
import { Effect } from 'effect';
import { Http, NodeHttpServer, NodeRuntime } from '@effect/platform-node';
import { Schema } from '@effect/schema';

// Define the expected schema for the user creation request body
const UserSchema = Schema.struct({
  name: Schema.string,
  email: Schema.string
});

const createUserRoute = Http.router.post(
  '/users',
  Http.request.schemaBodyJson(UserSchema).pipe(
    Effect.flatMap((body) => {
      // body is now guaranteed to be of type { name: string; email: string; }
      return Http.response.text(`Successfully created user: ${body.name}`);
    })
  )
);

const app = Http.router.empty.pipe(Http.router.addRoute(createUserRoute));

const program = Http.server.serve(app).pipe(
  Effect.provide(NodeHttpServer.layer({ port: 3000 }))
);

NodeRuntime.runMain(program);
```

