### Anti-Pattern: Using try/catch in Effect Compositions

Source: https://github.com/pauljphilp/effectpatterns/blob/main/rules/rules.md

This snippet highlights an anti-pattern in Effect.js development: the use of raw `try/catch` blocks within Effect compositions. This approach bypasses Effect's structured, type-safe error handling mechanisms, breaking the declarative flow and reducing the overall resilience and predictability of the application. It is recommended to use Effect's built-in error handling utilities like `catchTags` instead.

```typescript
// Anti-Pattern: Using try/catch blocks inside your Effect compositions.
// This breaks the declarative flow and bypasses Effect's powerful, type-safe error channels.
```

