### Non-Interruption-Safe Resource Handling (Anti-Pattern)

Source: https://github.com/pauljphilp/effectpatterns/blob/main/content/published/safely-bracket-resource-usage.mdx

This example shows a common anti-pattern using `async/await` with a `try...finally` block for resource management. It is not interruption-safe, meaning the `finally` block might not execute if the fiber running the Promise is interrupted by Effect's concurrency model, potentially leading to resource leaks.

```typescript
// ANTI-PATTERN: Not interruption-safe
async function getUser() {
  const connection = await getDbConnectionPromise(); // acquire
  try {
    return await useConnectionPromise(connection); // use
  } finally {
    // This block may not run if the fiber is interrupted!
    await closeConnectionPromise(connection); // release
  }
}
```

